C programming is an ANSI/ISO standard and powerful programming language for developing real time applications.C programming language was developed by DENNIS RITCHIE
at Bell Laboratories in 1972.It was invented for implementing UNIX operating system.C programming is most widely used prograaming language till today all other programming languages like c plus plus ,java,c# and many other programming languages were developed
by using the concepts and featues of C.C programming is the basis for all other programming languages.

1)The c language is a structred oriented programming language. C language features were developed from an language called "B"(BASIC COMBINED PROGRAMMING LANGUAGE-BCPL).
2)C language was invented for implementing UNIX opertaing system.
3)In 1978, Dennis Ritchie and Brian Kernighan published the first edition "The C Programming Language" and commonly known as K&R C
4)In 1983,the American National Standars Institute (ANSI) established a committee to provide a modern ,comprehensive definition of C.The resulting definition,the ANSI standard, or "ANSI C", was completed late 1988.
